<br>
My friends and I killed so many sunflowers, lightcrawlers, aliens, and sun revenants/reavers to the East and North of the plateau believing that might be the right area.  Turns out it wasn't.  However, on the East side of the plateau there is a rare named lightcrawler that spawns called Sectoid.  He drops at least 3 very interesting items.<br>
<br>
1) Melee bracer, chain and plate classes as I recall.  AC 12, +2 to most stats.<br>
<br>
2) Silken Trance Cord (waist item).  wt. 0, Int and Wis casters only (I think), +3 int/wis, +6 MR, plus stats.<br>
<br>
3) Ring, AC4, +6 agi/dex<br>
<br>
So it wasn't a complete waste of time.  Got 2 bracers, 1 ring, and one belt.  First Sectoid dropped the bracer and ring, second Sectoid dropped the bracer and belt.  Needless to say, my pally and wizzy are happy.  Now if only I could get Glorious Sunflower to pop so my brother's bard and I can leave Scarlet Desert.<br>
