but since theres like 15 named leeches and only 7 static spawns (and 11 total..) they gotta share.   My theory is each static spawn has 2 guys, and the lore guy is one of the wanderers.  I have seen the same ones spawn at the same spots more than 2x... same thing with other static spots like in dawnshroud in the rockhopper/sambata caves.. the cunning rockhopper always spawns to the right of the elder rockhopper.. and the sambata veiled guide spawns right there too when theyre up.. and so on and so on.. but unfortunately most of these guys arent static spawns <br>
<br>
I've done some research here.. you figure almost all the species in a zone will have 15 different quest guys, one for each class (ya theres some exceptions, but over all this is the rounded out method)  for example, there will be 15 rockhoppers, 15 bugs, 15 stonegrabbers, 15 thought leeches, and 15 spire spirits in Mons letalis.... <br>
<br>
then in scarlet you have grol baku, vas ren, tro jeg, sun revenants, bloodtribes, lightcrawlers, sunflowers, cheetahs, and rockhoppers.. 15 of each<br>
<br>
twilight sea you have cral ligi, turtles, scavanger minnow, grol baku, vas ren, beetles, shadows (i think theres more than 15 of each on some of these not sure i havent finished the other zone lists other than scarlet, my home on the moon)<br>
<br>
dawnshroud you got stonegrabbers, rockhoppers, sambatas, wolves and zelniaks, about 15 of each<br>
<br>
tenebrous you got coterie, bats, meeda hune, grol baku, and cral ligi.. about 15 of each.<br>
<br>
Yea each zone has a couple of exceptions, dawnshroud has the golden mushroom, tenebrous has the light sonic wolf, twilight has a tro jeg, etc... but this is why you see that 5:5:9:5:9 pattern for the classes because basically theres on average one type of mob per class per zone.<br>
<br>
And just because one sees a vas ren waterlord in scarlet doesnt mean that there isnt one in twilight sea.. there are a few mobs that share names in different zones, like grol baku seer (although scarlet version is a mob for a different quest and doesnt have faction or loot), and several others like rockhoppers you'll see 2 or 3 different zones w/the same named mob that always drops something different in their respective zones.<br>
